A family of three including an aged father and two sons escaped death by the whiskers yesterday in Lagos when a truck rammed into a fence into the shop that shelters the family thereby inflicting injuries on their bodies. LEADERSHIP gathered that the accident occurred when an Iveco truck with number plate FKJ 500 XZ veered off the express road and hit the fence of Federal Airport Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) staff quarters where the victims lived. According to one of the National Union member who witnessed the incident, the accident was as a result of reckless driving which cause the truck to veer-off the road and consequently rammed into the fence leaving people injured. One of the survivors of the accident, Mustapha Ibrahim told LEADERSHIP, “I thought my daddy had died.” He added that ‘’I was observing the on -going Ramadan fasting even though i wasn’t feeling well, I stepped out of the shop to do one or two things then went  inside the shop and I heard the sound of a vehicle that seem to have lost its break and rammed into the fence that covered our shop and  fell on my father and brother. ‘’Luckily there were security personnel and the people inside the quarters that quickly came to our rescue with my father and elder brother under the debris of the blocks and they were quickly rushed to the hospital because they sustained injuries even though mine was just a bruise and not too serious as my brother sustained serious head injury and my father you could see blood all over his face as the people helped  rush them including the truck driver who also sustained injury to the near -by hospital.’’ 